<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>blindspot — Knowledge Resilience Report</title>
<style>
:root {
  --bg: #fafbfc;
  --fg: #0f172a;
  --muted: #64748b;
  --border: #e2e8f0;
  --card: #ffffff;
  --accent: #2563eb;
  --critical: #dc2626;
  --high: #d97706;
  --medium: #0891b2;
  --healthy: #16a34a;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; }
body {
  margin: 0;
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--fg);
  font: 14px/1.5 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
}
.container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 64px; }
header { padding-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 32px; }
header h1 { margin: 0 0 4px; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
header .tagline { margin: 0 0 12px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; }
header .meta { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; }
header .meta code { background: #f1f5f9; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; }
section { margin-bottom: 40px; }
h2 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
.group-title {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  margin: 48px 0 20px;
  padding-bottom: 10px;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
}
.group-title:first-of-type { margin-top: 24px; }
.cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
.card {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;
}
.card .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.card .value { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 4px; }
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
th { text-align: left; font-weight: 500; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; padding: 12px 16px; background: #f8fafc; }
td { padding: 12px 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
td code, code.path { font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 13px; }
.badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; }
.badge.critical { background: #fef2f2; color: var(--critical); }
.badge.high { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--high); }
.badge.medium { background: #ecfeff; color: var(--medium); }
.badge.healthy, .badge.low { background: #f0fdf4; color: var(--healthy); }
.empty { color: var(--muted); padding: 16px; text-align: center; background: var(--card); border: 1px dashed var(--border); border-radius: 8px; }
footer { margin-top: 48px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
footer p { margin: 4px 0; }
.note { background: #fff7ed; border-left: 3px solid var(--high); padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 4px; color: #92400e; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.resilience { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 1fr) 2fr; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.resilience .overall { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
.resilience .overall .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.resilience .overall .score { font-size: 56px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; margin-top: 4px; letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
.resilience .overall .band { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; }
.resilience .subs { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
.resilience .sub { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-style: solid; }
.resilience .sub .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.resilience .sub .value { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.band-strong { color: var(--healthy); border-left-color: var(--healthy); }
.band-moderate { color: var(--medium); border-left-color: var(--medium); }
.band-fragile { color: var(--high); border-left-color: var(--high); }
.band-critical { color: var(--critical); border-left-color: var(--critical); }
.resilience .summary { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin: 4px 2px 0; }
.letter-grade {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 8px;
  padding: 2px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.letter-grade-sub {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 6px;
  padding: 0 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
  color: var(--muted);
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.narrative { background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f0f9ff 0%, #ffffff 100%); border: 1px solid #bae6fd; border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px 28px; margin-bottom: 32px; }
.narrative .eyebrow { color: var(--accent); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.narrative .headline { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--fg); }
.narrative .body { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: #1e293b; }
.narrative .body p { margin: 0 0 10px; }
.narrative .footer-meta { margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid #e0f2fe; color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; }
.rationale { display: block; margin-top: 4px; color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 12px; }
.trend-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
.trend-bar { flex: 1; height: 6px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 200px; }
.trend-bar-fill { height: 100%; }
.trend-delta { font-weight: 600; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.delta-up { color: var(--healthy); }
.delta-down { color: var(--critical); }
.delta-flat { color: var(--muted); }
.mermaid-wrap {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.mermaid { font-size: 13px; }
.departure-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
.departure-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
.departure-who { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 14px; }
.departure-stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 10px; }
.departure-stat .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
.departure-stat .value { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.departure-stat .value.v-crit { color: var(--critical); }
.departure-services .label { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.departure-services ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; font-size: 13px; }
.departure-card-multi { grid-column: 1 / -1; border-color: var(--accent); border-width: 2px; }
.departure-people { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
.departure-pill { background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; }
.muted-suffix { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 12px; margin-left: 4px; }
.pattern-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; margin-right: 6px; }
.upgrade-hint { margin-top: 14px; padding: 10px 14px; background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04); border-left: 3px solid var(--muted); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); }
.upgrade-hint strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
.upgrade-hint code { background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; color: var(--fg); }
.upgrade-hint pre { background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06); padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; margin: 6px 0; overflow-x: auto; color: var(--fg); font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
.notice-box { background: #fff7ed; border: 1px solid #fed7aa; border-left: 3px solid var(--high); border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px 16px; color: #7c2d12; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; }
.notice-box strong { color: #7c2d12; }
.notice-box code { background: rgba(124, 45, 18, 0.08); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
.notice-box pre { background: rgba(124, 45, 18, 0.08); padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; margin: 6px 0; overflow-x: auto; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; color: #7c2d12; }
details.architecture-details { margin-top: 24px; }
details.architecture-details summary {
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--muted);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  padding-bottom: 8px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
details.architecture-details[open] summary { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
{% if ctx.module_graph and ctx.module_graph.edges %}
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@10/dist/mermaid.min.js"></script>
<script>mermaid.initialize({startOnLoad: true, theme: 'neutral', flowchart: {curve: 'basis'}});</script>
{% endif %}
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

<header>
  <h1>blindspot</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Knowledge resilience report</p>
  <p class="meta">
    Repository: <code>{{ ctx.repo_path }}</code><br>
    Generated {{ ctx.generated_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M %Z") }} ·
    window: last {{ ctx.since_days }} days ·
    blindspot v{{ ctx.blindspot_version }}
  </p>
</header>

{% if ctx.narrative %}
<div class="narrative">
  <div class="eyebrow">Executive summary</div>
  <p class="headline">{{ ctx.narrative.headline_action }}</p>
  <div class="body">
    {% for para in ctx.narrative.executive_summary.split("\n\n") %}
      {% if para.strip() %}<p>{{ para.strip() }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="footer-meta">
    Generated by {{ ctx.narrative.model or "LLM" }} · language: {{ ctx.narrative.language }} ·
    treat as advisory, verify against the data below.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.narrative.model == "rule-based" %}
  <div class="upgrade-hint">
    💡 <strong>Want a richer, prose-style executive summary?</strong>
    Add a cloud LLM key (Anthropic or OpenAI) to your scan:
    <pre>--api-key sk-ant-... --provider anthropic --model claude-sonnet-4-6</pre>
    or set <code>narrative.api_key</code> in <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>.
    Without a key, this rule-based narrator is used — deterministic,
    in-process, no network.
  </div>
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

<h1 class="group-title">TL;DR — Resilience score, top actions, trend</h1>

{% if ctx.resilience %}
{% set band_class = "band-" ~ ctx.resilience.band | lower %}
<section>
  <h2>Engineering Resilience Score</h2>
  <div class="resilience">
    <div class="overall">
      <div class="label">Overall</div>
      <div class="score {{ band_class }}">{{ ctx.resilience.overall }}<span style="font-size:22px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:500;">/100</span> <span class="letter-grade {{ band_class }}" title="Letter grade for the overall score">{{ ctx.resilience.overall_grade }}</span></div>
      <div class="band {{ band_class }}">{{ ctx.resilience.band }}</div>
    </div>
    <div class="subs">
      {% for label, val, grade in [
        ("Ownership", ctx.resilience.ownership, ctx.resilience.ownership_grade),
        ("Decay", ctx.resilience.decay, ctx.resilience.decay_grade),
        ("Review", ctx.resilience.review, ctx.resilience.review_grade)
      ] %}
      <div class="sub {% if val is none %}{% elif val >= 80 %}band-strong{% elif val >= 60 %}band-moderate{% elif val >= 40 %}band-fragile{% else %}band-critical{% endif %}">
        <div class="label">{{ label }}</div>
        <div class="value">{% if val is none %}<span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:16px;font-weight:400;">no data</span>{% else %}{{ val }} <span class="letter-grade-sub">{{ grade }}</span>{% endif %}</div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="summary">{{ ctx.resilience.summary }}</p>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.recommendations %}
<section>
  <h2>Recommended actions</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Concrete next steps derived from the signals in this report.
    Each action is tied to a specific finding — treat them as conversation starters
    with the team, not directives.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Priority</th>
      <th>Category</th>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Target</th>
      <th>Evidence</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for a in ctx.recommendations %}
      <tr>
        <td>
          {% set prio_color = ({"High": "critical", "Medium": "high", "Low": "medium"})[a.priority.value] %}
          <span class="badge {{ prio_color }}">{{ a.priority.value }}</span>
        </td>
        <td>{{ a.category.value }}</td>
        <td>
          {% if a.pattern %}
          <span class="pattern-badge" title="Recurring fragility pattern">{{ a.pattern.value }}</span>
          {% endif %}
          <strong>{{ a.title }}</strong>
          <div style="margin-top:4px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;">{{ a.description }}</div>
          {% if ctx.narrative and ctx.narrative.rationales.get(a.target) %}
          <span class="rationale">▸ {{ ctx.narrative.rationales[a.target] }}</span>
          {% endif %}
        </td>
        <td><code class="path">{{ a.target }}</code></td>
        <td style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);font-family:ui-monospace,monospace;">{{ a.evidence }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.trend and ctx.trend.snapshots %}
<section>
  <h2>Resilience trend</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Historical snapshots based on ownership + decay (review sub-score
    only applies to the present). Use this to see whether resilience is trending up
    or down over the window.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>As of</th>
      <th class="num">Overall</th>
      <th class="num">Ownership</th>
      <th class="num">Decay</th>
      <th>Band</th>
      <th></th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for snap in ctx.trend.snapshots %}
      {% set band_lc = snap.score.band | lower %}
      <tr>
        <td>{% if snap.days_ago == 0 %}now{% else %}{{ snap.days_ago }} days ago{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num band-{{ band_lc }}" style="font-weight:600;">{{ snap.score.overall }}</td>
        <td class="num">{% if snap.score.ownership is not none %}{{ snap.score.ownership }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num">{% if snap.score.decay is not none %}{{ snap.score.decay }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {% if snap.score.band == 'Strong' %}healthy{% elif snap.score.band == 'Moderate' %}medium{% elif snap.score.band == 'Fragile' %}high{% else %}critical{% endif %}">{{ snap.score.band }}</span></td>
        <td>
          <div class="trend-bar">
            <div class="trend-bar-fill band-{{ band_lc }}" style="width: {{ snap.score.overall }}%; background: currentColor;"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% if ctx.trend.delta_overall is not none %}
  <p class="summary" style="margin-top:12px;">
    Change vs oldest snapshot:
    {% if ctx.trend.delta_overall > 0 %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-up">▲ +{{ ctx.trend.delta_overall }}</span> — improving.
    {% elif ctx.trend.delta_overall < 0 %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-down">▼ {{ ctx.trend.delta_overall }}</span> — declining.
    {% else %}
      <span class="trend-delta delta-flat">— flat</span>.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

<h1 class="group-title">People &amp; Ownership</h1>

<section>
  <h2>Service risk map</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Bus factor measures how many people would need to leave before knowledge of a service is critically lost.
    A bus factor of 1 means a single person carries the service.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.services %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Service</th><th class="num">Files</th><th class="num">Bus factor</th>
      <th>Risk</th><th>Top owner</th><th class="num">Their coverage</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in ctx.services %}
      <tr>
        <td><code>{{ s.service }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.file_count }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.bus_factor }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ s.risk_level }}">{{ s.risk_level }}</span></td>
        <td>{% if s.top_owners %}{{ ctx.label(s.top_owners[0][0]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num">{% if s.top_owners %}{{ s.top_owners[0][1] | pct }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No services analyzed in this window.</div>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Files with single ownership</h2>
  <p class="note">
    These files are entirely owned by one person. They are the most acute knowledge risk.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.critical_files %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Owner</th><th class="num">Coverage</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in ctx.critical_files %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ f.file }}</code></td>
        <td>{{ ctx.label(f.top_owners[0][0]) }}</td>
        <td class="num"><span class="badge critical">{{ f.top_owners[0][1] | pct }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No critical single-owner files detected.</div>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{% if ctx.departure_scenarios %}
<section>
  <h2>Departure scenarios — what we lose if one person leaves</h2>
  <p class="note">
    For each of the top contributors by aggregate ownership coverage, this
    is what would happen if they left tomorrow: how many files lose their
    primary expert, how many become unowned (orphan, top remaining
    coverage &lt; 30%), and which services take the largest hit. Use this
    to prioritise pair-work and knowledge transfer.
  </p>
  <div class="departure-grid">
    {% for scenario in ctx.departure_scenarios %}
    {% set svc_top = scenario.services[:3] %}
    {% set orphan_pct = (scenario.orphaned_files / scenario.total_files) if scenario.total_files else 0 %}
    {% set sev = "critical" if scenario.orphaned_files > 0 else ("high" if scenario.avg_coverage_loss > 0.30 else "medium") %}
    {% set is_multi = scenario.departing | length > 1 %}
    <div class="departure-card{% if is_multi %} departure-card-multi{% endif %}">
      <div class="departure-who">
        <span class="badge {{ sev }}">{{ sev | upper }}</span>
        {% if is_multi %}
        <strong>If {{ scenario.departing | length }} people leave together</strong>
        {% else %}
        <strong>If {{ ctx.label(scenario.departing[0]) }} leaves</strong>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      {% if is_multi %}
      <div class="departure-people">
        {% for email in scenario.departing %}
          <span class="departure-pill">{{ ctx.label(email) }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="departure-stats">
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Files affected</div>
          <div class="value">{{ scenario.affected_files }}<span class="muted-suffix"> / {{ scenario.total_files }}</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Orphan files</div>
          <div class="value{% if scenario.orphaned_files %} v-crit{% endif %}">{{ scenario.orphaned_files }}<span class="muted-suffix"> ({{ orphan_pct | pct }})</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="departure-stat">
          <div class="label">Avg coverage loss</div>
          <div class="value">{{ scenario.avg_coverage_loss | pct }}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% if svc_top %}
      <div class="departure-services">
        <div class="label">Most-affected services</div>
        <ul>
        {% for s in svc_top %}
          <li>
            <code class="path">{{ s.service }}</code>
            <span class="muted-suffix">{{ s.affected_files }}/{{ s.file_count }} files
              {%- if s.orphaned_files %}, {{ s.orphaned_files }} orphan{%- endif -%}
              , {{ s.avg_coverage_loss | pct }} avg loss</span>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<h1 class="group-title">Knowledge State</h1>

<section>
  <h2>Knowledge decay — top concerns</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Decay rises when an owner stops touching a file and others have been changing it.
    The 90-day projection shows the trajectory if nothing changes.
  </p>
  {% if ctx.decay_top %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th><th>Top owner</th>
      <th class="num">Days since touch</th>
      <th class="num">Decay score</th>
      <th>Risk</th>
      <th class="num">90-day projection</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for d in ctx.decay_top %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ d.file }}</code></td>
        <td>{{ ctx.label(d.top_owner) }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.days_since_owner_touch | days }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.decay_score | pct }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ d.risk_level }}">{{ d.risk_level }}</span></td>
        <td class="num">{{ d.projections[90] | pct }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No decay signals detected.</div>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{% if ctx.ai_readiness %}
<section>
  <h2>AI-native operational context</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Coverage of AI-readable organizational memory — agent rules, specs,
    prompts, architecture decisions, skills. Higher coverage means new
    contributors (human or AI) have more to load. This is not an
    AI-generated-code detector.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>Surface</th>
      <th>Agent rules</th>
      <th>Specs</th>
      <th>Prompts</th>
      <th>Architecture</th>
      <th>Skills</th>
      <th class="num">Coverage</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% set rows = [ctx.ai_readiness.repo] + (ctx.ai_readiness.services | list)[:10] %}
      {% for r in rows %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ r.target }}</td>
        <td>{% if r.agent_rules %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.specs %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.prompts %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.architecture %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td>{% if r.skills %}✓{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ (r.coverage_ratio * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

<h1 class="group-title">Process Quality</h1>

{% if not ctx.reviews_enabled and ctx.detected_remote %}
<section>
  <h2>Review lineage</h2>
  <div class="notice-box">
    🔌 <strong>Review metrics unavailable for this scan.</strong>
    {% if ctx.detected_remote == "github" %}
    A GitHub remote was detected, but no credentials were available.
    Enable it once and re-run the scan to unlock rubber-stamp ratio,
    reviewer diversity, fast-approval detection, and the PR activity mix:
    <pre>gh auth login                          # uses gh CLI (recommended)</pre>
    or pass a token directly:
    <pre>--github-token ghp_...</pre>
    or add it to <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>:
    <pre>github:
  token: ghp_...</pre>
    {% elif ctx.detected_remote == "bitbucket" %}
    A Bitbucket Cloud remote was detected, but no credentials were
    configured. Bitbucket Cloud has no anonymous access, so review
    metrics need an Atlassian API token (or legacy app password):
    <pre>--bitbucket-username you@email.com --bitbucket-app-password ATATT3...</pre>
    or add a block to <code>.blindspot.yaml</code>:
    <pre>bitbucket:
  username: you@email.com
  app_password: ATATT3...</pre>
    Create the token at <code>id.atlassian.com → API tokens</code> with
    <code>read:pullrequest:bitbucket</code> + <code>read:repository:bitbucket</code> scopes.
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.reviews_enabled %}
<section>
  <h2>Review lineage</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Review data fetched from GitHub ({{ ctx.pr_count }} PRs analyzed{% if ctx.pr_truncated %}, partial — rate limit hit{% endif %}).
    A rubber-stamp ratio is the share of approvals on a file that arrived without a single review comment.
    Reviewer diversity measures whether several people share the review load.
  </p>

  <h3 style="margin-top:24px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#475569;">Files with highest rubber-stamp ratio</h3>
  {% if ctx.top_rubber_stamps %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Reviewers</th>
      <th class="num">Reviews</th>
      <th class="num">Comments</th>
      <th class="num">Rubber-stamp</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in ctx.top_rubber_stamps %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ s.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.unique_reviewers }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_reviews }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_comments }}</td>
        <td class="num"><span class="badge {% if s.rubber_stamp_ratio >= 0.8 %}critical{% elif s.rubber_stamp_ratio >= 0.5 %}high{% else %}medium{% endif %}">{{ s.rubber_stamp_ratio | pct }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No rubber-stamp patterns detected.</div>
  {% endif %}

  <h3 style="margin-top:24px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#475569;">Files with lowest reviewer diversity</h3>
  {% if ctx.low_diversity_files %}
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Reviewers</th>
      <th class="num">Reviews</th>
      <th class="num">Diversity</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in ctx.low_diversity_files %}
      <tr>
        <td><code class="path">{{ s.file }}</code></td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.unique_reviewers }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ s.total_reviews }}</td>
        <td class="num"><span class="badge {% if s.diversity_hhi < 0.2 %}critical{% elif s.diversity_hhi < 0.5 %}high{% else %}medium{% endif %}">{{ s.diversity_hhi | pct }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <div class="empty">No low-diversity files detected.</div>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.correction_load_files %}
<section>
  <h2>Correction load</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Share of recent commits to each file that are follow-up fixes or reverts.
    A high ratio is observable evidence of <em>stability debt</em> — work is
    shipping but corrections are paying for it. Look at the surface, not the
    person.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr>
      <th>File</th>
      <th class="num">Total commits</th>
      <th class="num">Fixes</th>
      <th class="num">Reverts</th>
      <th class="num">Correction ratio</th>
      <th>Risk</th>
    </tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in ctx.correction_load_files[:10] %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ f.file }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.total_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.fix_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.revert_commits }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ f.correction_ratio | pct }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge {{ f.risk_level }}">{{ f.risk_level }}</span></td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% if ctx.module_graph and ctx.module_graph.edges %}
<details class="architecture-details">
  <summary>Architecture details — module dependency map</summary>
  <section style="margin-top:16px;">
    <p class="note">
      Top-level directories rolled up from the file dependency graph. Each
      node is a module ({{ ctx.module_graph.nodes | length }} shown, ranked by
      total connection weight); each edge is the count of file-level imports
      crossing between them. Arrows point from caller to callee.
    </p>
    <div class="mermaid-wrap">
      <pre class="mermaid">
graph LR
{% for n in ctx.module_graph.nodes -%}
  m_{{ n.name | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }}["{{ n.name }}<br/>{{ n.file_count }} file{% if n.file_count != 1 %}s{% endif %}"]
{% endfor -%}
{% for e in ctx.module_graph.edges -%}
  m_{{ e.from_module | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }} -->|{{ e.weight }}| m_{{ e.to_module | replace('/', '_') | replace('-', '_') | replace('.', '_') | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') }}
{% endfor -%}
      </pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</details>
{% endif %}

<footer>
  <p><strong>Methodology.</strong>
    Ownership is scored from commit count, change volume, recency, and review depth (review data pending).
    Decay combines code volatility since the owner's last touch with their absence over time.
    All metrics are evidence-derived; treat them as inputs to a conversation, not verdicts.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Privacy.</strong>
    Service-level views are the default. Individual data is shown only in service context and is
    intended for knowledge planning, not performance evaluation.
  </p>
  <p>blindspot v{{ ctx.blindspot_version }} · pre-alpha</p>
</footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
